  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "When shadowing traffic, Envoy adds `-shadow` to the end of the host string which is added as the `Host` header.\r\n\r\nIf you send to http://foobar:8000, Envoy will shadow that traffic and set the Header to `Host: foobar:8080-shadow`\r\n\r\nWith certain servlet containers (namely, Apache Tomcat), the protocol connector will try and parse the Host header and barf when it tries to parse the port as `8080-shadow` because of the non-integer characters.\r\n\r\nMaybe Envoy could set the `-shadow` postfix to the host part of the host/port pair?",
